    <h2>FAQs</h2>
    <div class="faq">
        <h3>Are Reese's Frozen Peanut Butter Dessert Cups gluten-free?</h3>
        <p>Reese's Frozen Peanut Butter Dessert Cups do not contain gluten ingredients, but they are not certified gluten-free. There is a risk of cross-contamination during manufacturing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
        <h3>Can people with celiac disease eat Reese's Frozen Peanut Butter Dessert Cups?</h3>
        <p>Individuals with celiac disease should exercise caution. While the product does not contain gluten ingredients, the risk of cross-contamination may be a concern for some.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq">
        <h3>What other Reese's products are gluten-free?</h3>
        <p>Reese's Pieces are considered gluten-free by the manufacturer. However, always check the label for the most accurate and up-to-date information.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>Reese's Frozen Peanut Butter Dessert Cups are a delicious treat that many people enjoy. For those who need to avoid gluten, the good news is that these dessert cups do not contain gluten ingredients. However, due to the potential for cross-contamination during manufacturing, they are not certified gluten-free. Individuals with celiac disease or severe gluten sensitivities should weigh the risks and consider their own tolerance levels before consuming these products. As always, it’s a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional if you have any concerns about your diet and gluten intake.</p>

